name: Beverly Hills Cop
summary: "Beverly Hills Cop: Axel F" has received mixed reviews from critics. While some praise Eddie Murphy's performance and the film's nostalgic appeal, others criticize its lack of originality and formulaic nature. Vulture calls it an "enjoyable retread," while Variety notes Murphy's efforts but acknowledges the sequel's reliance on nostalgia. The Hollywood Reporter finds the film "routine" and "low on new ideas." Keith & the Movies offers a more balanced take, praising Murphy's charm but expressing reservations about the film's overall execution. Roger Ebert's review is similarly conflicted, acknowledging Murphy's charisma but also criticizing the film's lack of substance. The New York Times dismisses it as "busted," while Forbes analyzes the film's plot and raises questions about Axel's fate. Decider recommends the film for its "mostly enjoyable" return of Murphy's iconic character, while Slate highlights the film's attempt to modernize the renegade police genre. The News Journal provides information on how to watch the film on Netflix.

name: Hurricane Beryl update
summary: Hurricane Beryl has caused significant damage and loss of life in the Caribbean region. name: Kamala Harris
summary: Recent polls and discussions have brought Kamala Harris's potential candidacy into the spotlight. A CNN poll suggests that voters perceive Democrats as having a better chance of retaining the White House if Biden is not nominated. Harris is seen as a possible replacement if Biden withdraws, with control over his campaign funds potentially falling into her hands. Several publications and experts have endorsed Harris as a formidable candidate, including The New York Times, New York Magazine, and The Bulwark. The Washington Post reports that Democrats are actively considering Harris as their primary candidate. A recent Ipsos in Canada poll places Harris as the preferred Democratic alternative to Biden in 2024, second only to Michelle Obama. The Wall Street Journal emphasizes Harris as Biden's most likely replacement, solidifying her position as a prominent figure in the upcoming election.

name: Oroville Fire
summary: Multiple articles report on the Thompson Fire, which is spreading quickly near Oroville, California. The fire has forced the evacuation of 13,000 residents and injured eight firefighters. The Los Angeles Times notes that the fire has spurred evacuations, while the Guardian US provides pictures of the fire's spread. The fire has also caused the cancellation of Oroville's Fourth of July firework celebration. Emergency declarations have been issued as the blaze continues to rage, prompting further evacuations. The fire has also burned structures, including homes. Officials have ordered evacuations in Butte County, where the fire has charred 3,000 acres of vegetation. The Thompson Fire has had a significant impact on the community, and authorities are working to control the blaze and ensure the safety of residents.

name: Michelle Obama
summary: According to polls, Michelle Obama is the only candidate who could defeat Donald Trump in the 2024 election, ahead of current President Biden. A significant number of Democrats believe Biden should withdraw from the race. Despite her popularity, Obama has expressed private frustrations with the Biden family and has no intention of replacing Biden as a candidate. While some believe her poll performance reflects her popularity and electability, others caution against assuming she would run or win an election. Some critics assert that backing Obama would aid Trump's chances, while others question the validity of her poll results.

name: Fashion Island
summary: Tragedy struck at Fashion Island in Newport Beach, California, when a woman was fatally shot during a robbery. The incident escalated when suspects attempted to flee the scene in a vehicle, striking and killing a 69-year-old tourist. As a result of the shooting and subsequent high-speed chase, one individual was killed, while the suspects remain at large. Authorities are actively searching for the perpetrators, and an investigation is ongoing to determine the circumstances surrounding this tragic event.
